-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The type I'm trying to use is from a web service, and the proxy code is like:

public class Course
{
	public int ID;
	public string Name;
	public string InstructorName;
	...etc...
}

The actual class behind the web service has private member fields and
public get/set properties, but the web reference proxy just generates public
fields.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Exposing public vields would be very valuable when using .NET web services and the proxy classes they generate. Right now converting the proxy classes to local classes is a huge pain in the neck. :)

I barely know how to *use* NVelocity, let alone know how to or have the time to hack on it, so I hope someone else can code this up. :)
